# Digest and Stats.xml – Technical Reference

Reference for digest generation, meter lookup, and 30-day meter tables. Use when modifying score display, meter parsing, or Stats.xml handling.

## Data Flow Overview

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    subgraph NewScores [New high scores]
        Diff[Stats.xml diff] --> ParseDiff[Get-NewScoreEntriesFromStatsDiff]
        ParseDiff --> MeterLookup[Get-MeterFromSongChart]
        MeterLookup --> DigestEntry[Digest line with meter]
    end
    
    subgraph AllScores [All songs completed]
        Stats[Full Stats.xml] --> ParseStats[Get-MeterTallyFromStatsXml]
        ParseStats --> FilterDate[DateTime >= cutoff]
        FilterDate --> MeterLookup2[Get-MeterFromSongChart]
        MeterLookup2 --> Tally[30-day meter table]
    end
```

## Digest Entries (New High Scores)

**Source:** Git diff of `LocalProfiles/*/Stats.xml` between backup runs.

**Flow:**
1. `Get-NewScoreEntriesFromStatsDiff` parses the diff for `<Song Dir="...">` blocks with `<Steps>` and `<HighScore>`.
2. For each new score, calls `Get-MeterFromSongChart` with `SongDir`, `Difficulty`, `StepsType`.
3. Formats as `**Player** set a new score for **Song** (Pack) - Difficulty (Meter), dance-single - X% DP on date.`

**Repair:** `Repair-DigestMeters` runs after digest write. For lines missing meters, uses `Parse-DigestScoreLineForMeterRepair` → `Get-SongFolderByPackAndName` → `Get-MeterFromSongFolder` to add meters to existing digest files.

## Meter Lookup

**Functions:** `Get-MeterFromSongChart`, `Get-MeterFromSongFolder`, `Get-SongFolderByPackAndName`

**Path resolution order:**
1. `InstallPath + SongDir` (e.g. `C:\ITGMania\Songs\Pack\Song`)
2. For `AdditionalSongs/` prefix: each path from `AdditionalSongFolderPaths` + suffix
3. If no `Songs/` or `AdditionalSongs/` prefix: try `InstallPath\Songs\SongDir`
4. **Fallback:** `Get-SongFolderByPackAndName` – search for `Pack/SongFolder` across all song roots (Songs, AdditionalSongs, AdditionalSongFolderPaths). Matches exact, StartsWith, or Contains.

**AdditionalSongFolderPaths:** From `config.json` `AdditionalSongFolderPaths` array, or parsed from `Preferences.ini` `AdditionalSongFolders` (Save folder, AppData, install root).

**Chart parsing:**
- **.ssc:** `#NOTEDATA:` blocks with `#STEPSTYPE`, `#DIFFICULTY`, `#METER`
- **.sm:** `#NOTES:` section. Standard format: `dance-single:`, `:`, `Medium:`, `8:` (type, description, difficulty, meter). Compact format: type, difficulty, meter. Parser tries both.

**Get-SongDisplayNameFromDir:** Splits `SongDir` on both `/` and `\` to extract Pack (second-to-last) and SongTitle (last). Handles Windows backslash paths.

## 30-Day Meter Tables

**Source:** Full `Stats.xml` files in staging (`SavePortable/LocalProfiles/*/Stats.xml`, `SaveAppData/LocalProfiles/*/Stats.xml`).

**Flow:** `Get-MeterTallyFromStatsXml` parses XML, iterates `//Song` → `Steps` → `HighScoreList/HighScore` (or `Steps/HighScore`). Filters by `DateTime >= CutoffDate`. For each, calls `Get-MeterFromSongChart`. Builds `@{ PlayerName => @{ Meter => Count } }`. Skips scores when meter lookup fails.

**Fallback:** When Stats.xml tally is empty (e.g. meter lookup fails for all songs), `Get-MeterTallyFromDigests` is used instead. It parses digest lines with `Parse-DigestScoreLine` (requires `Difficulty (Meter)` format) and counts scores from the last 30 digest files. Ensures charts always appear when digest data has meters.

**Deduplication:** Processes SavePortable first, then SaveAppData. Skips profile IDs already processed to avoid double-counting.

**Profile name:** From root `<Name>` in Stats.xml, or `"Profile " + profileId` if empty.

## Stats.xml Structure

```xml
<Stats>
  <Name>ProfileName</Name>
  <SongScores>
    <Song Dir="Songs/Pack/SongFolder">
      <Steps Difficulty="Challenge" StepsType="dance-single">
        <HighScoreList>
          <HighScore>
            <DateTime>2024-01-15T12:30:00</DateTime>
            ...
          </HighScore>
        </HighScoreList>
      </Steps>
    </Song>
  </SongScores>
</Stats>
```

